{
 "name": "RPlog_Lecture_on_Imperial_Leadership",
 "title": "Lecture on Imperial Leadership",
 "summary": "Commodore Krieg Inrokana convenes the first of his task-force training sessions, turning his office into a classroom to lecture on leadership, discipline, and professionalism in the Imperial military. Lieutenant Vextin Mandor, the ISB cadet Ashden, and pilot Liza Molokai attend and offer their views. Using Liza's recent costly ambush as a case study, Krieg argues that blind obedience is as dangerous as cowardice, urging his officers to think for themselves and flex their orders to achieve objectives -- likening a good commander to a surgeon who strikes vital points rather than dulling the blade. Vextin extols drilled discipline while the fanatically loyal Ashden defends absolute obedience, and Krieg closes the session hinting at a major operation to come.",
